sql:
SELECT jp.job_title, a.candidate_name, a.status
FROM applications AS a
JOIN job_postings AS jp ON a.job_id = jp.job_id;

external_knowledge:
- "blossoming career oases" refers to active job postings;
- "sprouting for how long" refers to the duration since the job was posted;
- "first seeds of interest" refers to the first application submitted for each job;
- "saplings reaching for the sky" metaphorically refers to active applications that are currently in the "submitted" status.

- "Sown the seeds" metaphorically refers to managing applications;
- "Watered by a phone call" means the applications included at least one phone call communication;
- "Dawn and dusk of the first half of 2023" refers to the period from January 1, 2023, to June 30, 2023.
